1
00:00:03,086 --> 00:00:05,172
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:22,374 --> 00:01:28,297
DECISION

3
00:01:34,261 --> 00:01:36,513
DEATH NOTE

4
00:01:39,224 --> 00:01:41,977
I hereby relinquish ownership
of this Death Note

5
00:01:43,562 --> 00:01:44,855
Take care of her.

6
00:01:45,147 --> 00:01:46,481
You gave your word.

7
00:01:57,618 --> 00:01:58,785
[whimpers quietly]

8
00:02:03,498 --> 00:02:04,875
[moans]

9
00:02:05,083 --> 00:02:06,501
[Misa] Mr. Stalker.

10
00:02:07,044 --> 00:02:08,378
Hello, Mister.

11
00:02:08,545 --> 00:02:10,088
Where are you right now?

12
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:12,716
Do-- do you think we could stop this game?

13
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,885
-[Matsuda] Huh?
-[Aizawa] "Stalker?"

14
00:02:14,968 --> 00:02:16,470
Where did she get that?

15
00:02:16,928 --> 00:02:18,930
What's with the new attitude
all of a sudden?

16
00:02:26,188 --> 00:02:27,230
Just as I thought.

17
00:02:27,314 --> 00:02:29,274
As long as I still have Ryuk's notebook,

18
00:02:29,483 --> 00:02:31,151
even though I gave up Rem's,

19
00:02:31,234 --> 00:02:33,779
all awareness I have of Rem still remains.

20
00:02:34,112 --> 00:02:35,155
Rem.

21
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:37,699
The only reason I have to go through
all this trouble

22
00:02:37,783 --> 00:02:40,786
is because you brought another Death Note
to the human world.

23
00:02:42,537 --> 00:02:44,915
Is this really what you want, Light?

24
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:46,291
Yeah.

25
00:02:47,918 --> 00:02:50,879
Okay. I never thought
the Death Note I gave you

26
00:02:50,962 --> 00:02:53,298
would end up buried and abandoned.

27
00:02:53,924 --> 00:02:55,133
Listen, Ryuk,

28
00:02:55,384 --> 00:02:57,803
for the time being
I'm just hiding it, but...

29
00:02:58,220 --> 00:02:59,304
it stays mine.

30
00:03:00,055 --> 00:03:03,141
Until the next time
you hear me say the following words:

31
00:03:03,266 --> 00:03:04,810
get rid of it.

32
00:03:04,976 --> 00:03:05,977
When I say that,

33
00:03:06,061 --> 00:03:07,479
regardless of the context,

34
00:03:07,646 --> 00:03:10,440
assume that I want to relinquish
ownership of this Death Note.

35
00:03:10,691 --> 00:03:11,692
Got it.

36
00:03:12,317 --> 00:03:15,529
Mr. Stalker, this is illegal.
You have to stop.

37
00:03:16,071 --> 00:03:17,823
Okay. Come on, please.

38
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:19,658
She's been acting like this

39
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:21,868
ever since she regained consciousness.

40
00:03:22,202 --> 00:03:23,203
[Matsuda] Seriously.

41
00:03:23,328 --> 00:03:25,831
Does she think she can get out of this
just by playing dumb?

42
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:27,749
[Misa] Okay. How about this?

43
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:30,669
You could at least take off my blindfold,
don't you think?

44
00:03:30,961 --> 00:03:32,879
It would be nice to see
what you look like.

45
00:03:35,132 --> 00:03:37,008
Matsuda, call Mogi for me.

46
00:03:37,259 --> 00:03:38,135
Huh?

47
00:03:38,427 --> 00:03:39,594
Just a second.

48
00:03:40,095 --> 00:03:41,096
[phone keys beep]

49
00:03:41,179 --> 00:03:42,222
Here.

50
00:03:42,347 --> 00:03:45,183
Mr. Mogi, when you apprehended Misa Amane,

51
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:47,561
you made it clear
that she was a suspect. Am I correct?

52
00:03:47,978 --> 00:03:49,980
Yes. Like you told me.

53
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:52,816
First, I blindfolded her
and covered her mouth.

54
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:55,152
I... told her we knew
she was the Second Kira.

55
00:03:55,444 --> 00:03:57,320
I made sure that she heard me.

56
00:03:57,487 --> 00:04:00,365
She didn't struggle when I
put the blindfold and handcuffs on her.

57
00:04:00,490 --> 00:04:02,617
It was like... she accepted it.

58
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:05,746
What if I give you an autograph
or shake your hand?

59
00:04:05,829 --> 00:04:08,415
I know! I can give you
a kiss on the cheek if you want.

60
00:04:08,915 --> 00:04:11,251
Oh, come on. I won't run away. I promise.

61
00:04:12,294 --> 00:04:14,296
We've already made
so much progress with her.

62
00:04:14,421 --> 00:04:15,964
I actually thought she'd crack.

63
00:04:16,298 --> 00:04:18,467
Why is she suddenly talking
about a stalker?

64
00:04:20,594 --> 00:04:22,471
-[L] [modified voice] Misa Amane.
-[Misa] Huh?

65
00:04:22,596 --> 00:04:24,097
What's that, Mr. Stalker?

66
00:04:24,514 --> 00:04:25,932
Are you planning to release me?

67
00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:28,727
[L] [modified voice] Before you
passed out, you barely spoke.

68
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:30,520
And you even asked me to kill you.

69
00:04:30,645 --> 00:04:32,689
And now you're claiming ignorance?

70
00:04:32,773 --> 00:04:34,524
Hm? I don't understand.

71
00:04:34,858 --> 00:04:38,236
I mean, you're the one who knocked me out
and brought me here, remember?

72
00:04:38,528 --> 00:04:39,446
Wait?

73
00:04:39,529 --> 00:04:43,492
I get it. This is some kind of Misa Amane
interrogation fantasy, right?

74
00:04:45,494 --> 00:04:48,371
Do you know why I'm detaining you here?
You must have some idea.

75
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:51,291
[Misa] What do you mean?
Because I'm a celebrity, obviously.

76
00:04:52,042 --> 00:04:54,669
But you’re definitely the first stalker
who's ever gone this far.

77
00:04:54,795 --> 00:04:56,505
And you're starting to scare me.

78
00:04:57,839 --> 00:05:00,467
Hey, Amane, no one is buying this!
So, cut it out!

79
00:05:01,635 --> 00:05:03,929
Oh. This is scary. What's going on?

80
00:05:04,012 --> 00:05:06,515
I can't stand it anymore!
Please, let me go!

81
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,433
You have to me go!

82
00:05:08,517 --> 00:05:10,435
Oh, I need to go to the bathroom.

83
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:12,437
I have to go to the bathroom again! Okay?

84
00:05:12,521 --> 00:05:14,272
[L] [modified voice]
It's only been four minutes

85
00:05:14,356 --> 00:05:17,776
since you last went to the bathroom.
I'm afraid, you'll have to hold it.

86
00:05:18,109 --> 00:05:19,277
You have to!

87
00:05:19,402 --> 00:05:21,780
It's the only time you'll untie me
and let me move!

88
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,490
Plus, you'll be able to watch.

89
00:05:23,573 --> 00:05:25,742
Isn't that what you want, isn't it?

90
00:05:25,951 --> 00:05:27,035
You pervert!

91
00:05:27,828 --> 00:05:30,080
I'm a... pervert?

92
00:05:31,122 --> 00:05:34,084
Amane, let's get back to the conversation
we were having

93
00:05:34,209 --> 00:05:35,919
before you lost consciousness.

94
00:05:36,545 --> 00:05:38,588
First of all,
do you know who Light Yagami is?

95
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:40,465
And if so, why did you approach him?

96
00:05:40,632 --> 00:05:41,591
Huh?

97
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:45,053
What do you mean?
How can I not know my own boyfriend?

98
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:47,138
[L] She was so tight-lipped
about it earlier,

99
00:05:47,264 --> 00:05:49,599
but now she's openly admitting
he's her boyfriend?

100
00:05:49,808 --> 00:05:51,184
Where is this coming from?

101
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:53,019
-[phone ringing]
-[L] Huh?

102
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:55,272
Good timing. It's Light.

103
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:58,358
Please, turn the video and audio off.

104
00:05:58,441 --> 00:06:00,068
-[Yagami] Yes.
-[phone ringing]

105
00:06:01,278 --> 00:06:03,238
[L] Yes. Yes, I understand.

106
00:06:03,488 --> 00:06:05,699
We will be expecting you in room K2801.

107
00:06:07,325 --> 00:06:09,619
Are you saying my son's coming here?

108
00:06:13,790 --> 00:06:17,252
[footsteps]

109
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:26,344
Ryuzaki, like I said over the phone,

110
00:06:27,304 --> 00:06:29,097
I could be Kira.

111
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:30,348
[gasps]

112
00:06:30,849 --> 00:06:32,183
No, Light!

113
00:06:32,309 --> 00:06:33,810
What are you talking about?

114
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:36,938
Why would you even say
something like that? Why?

115
00:06:37,439 --> 00:06:40,066
[L] There's no real proof
that Light Yagami is Kira,

116
00:06:40,191 --> 00:06:43,528
why come here to announce
that you could be Kira?

117
00:06:44,362 --> 00:06:45,363
It's an act.

118
00:06:45,488 --> 00:06:48,033
There's no "could be" about it.
You are Kira.

119
00:06:48,366 --> 00:06:50,493
What do you hope
to accomplish by this?

120
00:06:51,369 --> 00:06:53,788
Look, Dad, if Ryuzaki is L,

121
00:06:53,872 --> 00:06:56,374
then it's safe to say
that he is the world's best detective.

122
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:59,169
And right now, he seems pretty sure
that I'm Kira.

123
00:06:59,753 --> 00:07:01,963
We know L's never been wrong before.

124
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:04,966
Wha-- What are you saying, Light?
Stop this!

125
00:07:05,383 --> 00:07:08,386
[Light] What about that FBI agent,
Raye Penber?

126
00:07:08,470 --> 00:07:11,681
It was me he was investigating
immediately before he died.

127
00:07:12,015 --> 00:07:14,351
And I was in Aoyama on May 22nd.

128
00:07:14,517 --> 00:07:16,811
Also, I'm the first person
in the Kanto region

129
00:07:16,937 --> 00:07:19,981
that Misa, the alleged
Second Kira, approached.

130
00:07:20,231 --> 00:07:21,691
It's all been me.

131
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:27,072
If I were in L's place, even I
would have come to the same conclusion.

132
00:07:27,739 --> 00:07:31,034
You see, subconsciously I might be Kira.

133
00:07:31,368 --> 00:07:34,120
If that were the case,
I could be him and not even know it.

134
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:35,664
No, Light.

135
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:37,332
[L] I see.

136
00:07:37,415 --> 00:07:39,459
So, you're not conscious of it, huh?

137
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:43,171
I... I'm not sure of anything anymore.

138
00:07:43,505 --> 00:07:45,215
I'd never kill someone, but...

139
00:07:45,632 --> 00:07:48,134
unconsciously, who knows
what I'm capable of?

140
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:50,720
Another me could be killing people
as I sleep.

141
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:52,305
I'm afraid that's not possible.

142
00:07:52,722 --> 00:07:54,933
Huh? Not possible? What do you mean?

143
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:56,851
Well, I never mentioned this to you,

144
00:07:56,977 --> 00:07:59,104
but at one point I had hidden
surveillance cameras

145
00:07:59,229 --> 00:08:00,897
installed in your room for five days.

146
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:02,649
Cameras?

147
00:08:02,899 --> 00:08:03,942
Yes.

148
00:08:04,401 --> 00:08:06,987
Every single night you slept normally.

149
00:08:07,946 --> 00:08:10,365
Criminals, whose names were broadcast,
were still dying,

150
00:08:10,532 --> 00:08:12,867
even though you would have had no way
of knowing about them.

151
00:08:13,034 --> 00:08:15,161
But this didn't prove your innocence
to me.

152
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:17,956
All it proved was
that if you were Kira,

153
00:08:18,081 --> 00:08:20,417
no amount of camera surveillance
would reveal that fact.

154
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:23,253
Wouldn't reveal that fact, huh?

155
00:08:24,713 --> 00:08:26,840
I... don't know. It could be true.

156
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:28,591
I have to admit,

157
00:08:28,717 --> 00:08:30,760
I've found myself thinking that…

158
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:32,762
some criminals deserve to die.

159
00:08:33,263 --> 00:08:35,557
If I can think like Kira,
than how can I be sure

160
00:08:35,849 --> 00:08:37,726
that I'm not actually him.

161
00:08:38,101 --> 00:08:39,227
Hold on, Light!

162
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:41,062
I feel exactly the same way.

163
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:45,066
I've found myself thinking before
that some people would be better off dead.

164
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:47,902
But still, that doesn't mean
we're gonna go out and kill people.

165
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:49,195
Isn't that right?

166
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:53,241
Besides, criminals were still being killed
even while you had no knowledge of them.

167
00:08:53,616 --> 00:08:56,119
I mean, the surveillance cameras
proved it, didn't they?

168
00:08:56,661 --> 00:08:57,620
Well, no.

169
00:08:57,954 --> 00:09:00,081
Because we were
short of investigators then,

170
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:01,875
we only watched him while he was at home.

171
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:05,545
Truth is, we weren't able to watch him
every hour of the day.

172
00:09:06,004 --> 00:09:07,839
It's possible he could've found some way

173
00:09:08,006 --> 00:09:10,175
to kill those criminals
while he wasn't at home.

174
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:14,679
[L] This was premeditated.

175
00:09:14,929 --> 00:09:17,265
It's no accident you chose to do this now.

176
00:09:18,016 --> 00:09:20,685
Well, what if we incarcerate
you for a while?

177
00:09:20,977 --> 00:09:22,771
Imprison you, like we did Amane.

178
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:25,857
If criminals whose names were made public,
keep dying,

179
00:09:26,691 --> 00:09:30,111
then it would lead us to think
that you're innocent, right?

180
00:09:31,946 --> 00:09:33,531
Is that how you imagined it?

181
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:36,868
[Yagami grunts]

182
00:09:38,870 --> 00:09:41,539
[L] Honestly, I don't like the way
that this is going at all.

183
00:09:41,664 --> 00:09:43,166
But what choice do I have?

184
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:44,918
Let's do it.

185
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:45,919
[gasps]

186
00:09:46,294 --> 00:09:48,755
I need you to fully restrain Light Yagami

187
00:09:49,005 --> 00:09:50,673
and place him in solitary confinement.

188
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:52,050
What? You can't!

189
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:54,928
You want us to confine him? Seriously?

190
00:09:55,512 --> 00:09:58,056
[L] If we're gonna do this,
it has to happen immediately.

191
00:09:58,681 --> 00:10:01,726
From this point on you can't be allowed
to go anywhere where I can't see you.

192
00:10:01,810 --> 00:10:03,103
This is crazy!

193
00:10:03,311 --> 00:10:05,438
There's no way my son could be Kira.

194
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:07,440
My son is not capable of...

195
00:10:07,524 --> 00:10:08,775
[Light] It's okay, Dad.

196
00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:10,276
Stop this, Light.

197
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:11,528
Listen.

198
00:10:12,112 --> 00:10:13,947
Something has to be done about this.

199
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:16,241
As long as I'm having these doubts,

200
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:18,451
I can't work with you to catch Kira.

201
00:10:18,618 --> 00:10:19,953
But Ryuzaki,

202
00:10:20,161 --> 00:10:21,246
promise me this.

203
00:10:21,496 --> 00:10:24,749
Until you can say
with absolute certainty that I'm not Kira,

204
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:26,376
you cannot set me free,

205
00:10:26,459 --> 00:10:29,587
no matter what I might say,
or what condition I might be in.

206
00:10:30,421 --> 00:10:31,840
You have my word.

207
00:10:32,006 --> 00:10:36,010
Mr. Yagami, can you come up with some
sort of excuse for Light’s absence,

208
00:10:36,219 --> 00:10:37,720
something to tell your family?

209
00:10:37,929 --> 00:10:39,597
And... please, do it now.

210
00:10:39,764 --> 00:10:42,433
But... this is all so sudden.
What should I say?

211
00:10:42,851 --> 00:10:44,936
And I see no reason
why he should be in prison.

212
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:46,354
-Let it go, Dad.
-Huh?

213
00:10:46,688 --> 00:10:49,524
If I don't do this,
I won't be able to live with myself.

214
00:10:50,191 --> 00:10:52,777
But son, do you really... mean that?

215
00:10:53,361 --> 00:10:54,404
Yeah.

216
00:10:54,696 --> 00:10:57,115
I believe that by giving up
my very freedom,

217
00:10:57,407 --> 00:11:00,076
I'll defeat this fear
that Kira lurks within me.

218
00:11:01,744 --> 00:11:03,705
[L] Aizawa, please, take him away.

219
00:11:04,122 --> 00:11:05,165
Right.

220
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:35,236
[prison gates slam]

221
00:11:37,864 --> 00:11:40,658
FIRST DAY IN PRISON

222
00:11:40,783 --> 00:11:43,077
Next, I just have to
get rid of the notebook.

223
00:11:43,244 --> 00:11:46,206
So, I guess apples
are out of the question?

224
00:11:57,050 --> 00:11:58,009
Ryuzaki.

225
00:11:58,509 --> 00:12:01,471
I'd like to request that you take me
off this investigation.

226
00:12:01,596 --> 00:12:02,555
-Chief!
-But why?

227
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:04,515
I've thought about this and the fact is

228
00:12:04,599 --> 00:12:07,101
that we're holding my son, Light,
as a prime suspect.

229
00:12:07,352 --> 00:12:09,979
Given that, it's not appropriate for me
to be here.

230
00:12:10,772 --> 00:12:12,315
When we spoke earlier,

231
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:14,150
my feelings got in the way.

232
00:12:14,275 --> 00:12:17,820
It's impossible for me to be objective
in this situation.

233
00:12:18,321 --> 00:12:19,447
I agree with you.

234
00:12:19,656 --> 00:12:21,908
We can't let personal feelings
get in the way.

235
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:24,369
And in truth... if...

236
00:12:24,786 --> 00:12:27,413
if the task force concludes
that my son is Kira,

237
00:12:27,622 --> 00:12:29,707
I don't know what I'd be capable of.

238
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:32,085
[L] Yes, I'll agree with you there.

239
00:12:32,210 --> 00:12:34,420
To be honest,
I wondered what you might do.

240
00:12:34,712 --> 00:12:37,090
I believe you'd kill your son
and then yourself.

241
00:12:38,466 --> 00:12:39,634
I'd also agree that it's best

242
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:41,761
that we don't have you
working here for now.

243
00:12:43,721 --> 00:12:44,722
Ryuzaki!

244
00:12:44,847 --> 00:12:47,433
I will ask that you confine me as well.

245
00:12:47,684 --> 00:12:49,435
At the moment, I'm calm,

246
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:52,772
but to be honest, I'm not sure
how much more of this I can take.

247
00:12:52,855 --> 00:12:54,983
I thought you might say that,
so I spoke with Watari.

248
00:12:55,233 --> 00:12:56,567
He's made arrangements.

249
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:58,236
[Matsuda and Aizawa] Huh?

250
00:12:59,654 --> 00:13:02,949
Mm-hm. But your confinement
will be different.

251
00:13:03,491 --> 00:13:05,410
You will keep your cell phone turned on

252
00:13:05,535 --> 00:13:08,663
and maintain regular contact
with family and friends.

253
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:10,790
You won't tell Light about this.

254
00:13:11,249 --> 00:13:12,709
If he does call you at some point,

255
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:15,712
he must be made to believe
that you're still at headquarters.

256
00:13:17,255 --> 00:13:18,798
While you are in confinement,

257
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:21,634
we'll be giving you
continuous updates on the investigation.

258
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:23,261
so you'll know what's happening.

259
00:13:25,388 --> 00:13:26,681
So, how does that sound to you?

260
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:28,599
I'm grateful.

261
00:13:28,975 --> 00:13:30,101
Thank you.

262
00:13:31,894 --> 00:13:34,605
THIRD DAY IN PRISON

263
00:13:38,568 --> 00:13:41,237
[Misa] Hey, Mister,
I really wanna take a bath.

264
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:44,365
I'm pretty sure you already know
where I live, don't you?

265
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:46,451
Could you bring me some clean clothes?

266
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:49,704
I didn't think this could get
any more bizarre.

267
00:13:49,996 --> 00:13:52,540
I feel so sorry for the Chief right now.

268
00:13:55,501 --> 00:13:57,086
Ryuzaki, talk to me.

269
00:13:57,253 --> 00:13:58,296
What's happening?

270
00:13:58,463 --> 00:14:00,298
Have any new criminals been identified?

271
00:14:00,423 --> 00:14:02,592
Anyone that Kira would be
likely to target?

272
00:14:03,009 --> 00:14:04,969
If so, has he killed any of them?

273
00:14:06,929 --> 00:14:10,350
In fact, quite a few criminals' names
have been broadcast recently.

274
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,352
But since you've been detained

275
00:14:12,602 --> 00:14:15,355
we haven't had one report
of a criminal being killed by Kira.

276
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:17,482
Wait, no one's been killed?

277
00:14:17,774 --> 00:14:18,733
Really?

278
00:14:19,067 --> 00:14:19,942
[L] Yes.

279
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:21,694
I see.

280
00:14:22,028 --> 00:14:24,947
So, it's only a matter of time
before I'm convicted as Kira.

281
00:14:25,239 --> 00:14:27,158
What I wouldn't give for an apple...

282
00:14:28,201 --> 00:14:29,702
[L] What's going on here?

283
00:14:30,370 --> 00:14:33,664
I thought the murders would continue
even after Light was confined.

284
00:14:33,956 --> 00:14:35,208
Instead...

285
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:37,377
they've stopped completely.

286
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:41,297
Light asked to be confined
in the first place.

287
00:14:41,923 --> 00:14:43,216
If this continues,

288
00:14:43,341 --> 00:14:46,052
it will only strengthen
the argument that he is Kira.

289
00:14:47,178 --> 00:14:48,262
The only question left

290
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:51,516
will be whether or not
he was conscious of being Kira.

291
00:14:52,642 --> 00:14:54,394
Does he really think that's gonna work?

292
00:14:54,936 --> 00:14:56,479
That he will be let off the hook,

293
00:14:56,604 --> 00:14:59,482
if he can just prove
he wasn't conscious of being Kira?

294
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:02,151
It's not like Light Yagami.

295
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:04,195
No, it's not like Kira.

296
00:15:05,488 --> 00:15:08,324
FIFTH DAY IN PRISON

297
00:15:09,659 --> 00:15:11,327
I can't take this anymore.

298
00:15:11,536 --> 00:15:13,454
If I don't get an apple soon,
I don't know...

299
00:15:13,788 --> 00:15:15,873
In the end, I just have
to get through this.

300
00:15:15,998 --> 00:15:16,916
No matter what.

301
00:15:17,542 --> 00:15:19,210
You know what, Mr. Stalker,

302
00:15:19,669 --> 00:15:23,214
your video won't sell if it's just me
sitting here the whole time.

303
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:28,428
[L] Mr. Yagami looks pretty bad.

304
00:15:28,636 --> 00:15:30,888
I think he's taking this harder
than Light or Misa.

305
00:15:31,055 --> 00:15:32,306
[Matsuda] What do you expect?

306
00:15:32,432 --> 00:15:34,600
It's been five days
since Light was put in prison.

307
00:15:34,934 --> 00:15:38,896
And look, not a single criminal
whose name has been broadcast was killed.

308
00:15:39,772 --> 00:15:41,023
In these situations

309
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:43,192
I think the parents must suffer
a lot more than the accused.

310
00:15:43,651 --> 00:15:44,569
[Aizawa] No kidding.

311
00:15:44,694 --> 00:15:47,238
Especially now that we're seeing proof
that Light is Kira.

312
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:50,116
Mr. Yagami.

313
00:15:50,533 --> 00:15:52,118
What is it? Is it good news?

314
00:15:52,285 --> 00:15:53,327
Is it bad news?

315
00:15:53,494 --> 00:15:54,662
[Matsuda and Aizawa groan]

316
00:15:54,871 --> 00:15:57,790
No. I wanted to tell you
not to worry so much.

317
00:15:58,416 --> 00:16:01,043
It doesn't matter how much time
you devote to worrying about this.

318
00:16:01,461 --> 00:16:02,837
The outcome will be the same.

319
00:16:03,004 --> 00:16:05,089
This could go on for quite some time.

320
00:16:05,298 --> 00:16:07,383
Perhaps you should rest
in a more comfortable place.

321
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:10,636
Impossible!
What makes you think I care where I am?

322
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:12,096
It won't change anything.

323
00:16:12,305 --> 00:16:15,141
With the state I'm in now,
this is the best place for me.

324
00:16:15,308 --> 00:16:17,018
And no matter what the results,

325
00:16:17,143 --> 00:16:20,229
when I leave here
it's going to be with my son.

326
00:16:21,856 --> 00:16:23,024
I understand.

327
00:16:23,983 --> 00:16:26,527
SEVENTH DAY IN PRISON

328
00:16:35,953 --> 00:16:38,039
Light, you've only been here
for one week,

329
00:16:38,164 --> 00:16:39,540
but I'm sure it can't be easy.

330
00:16:40,291 --> 00:16:41,375
Are you feeling all right?

331
00:16:45,713 --> 00:16:47,381
[Light] Now, that I've come this far,

332
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:49,383
I think it's about time.

333
00:16:55,765 --> 00:16:58,476
Yeah, I know I must look
pretty bad in here,

334
00:16:58,643 --> 00:17:00,228
but this useless pride...

335
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:02,355
I suppose I'll have to...

336
00:17:03,814 --> 00:17:04,774
get rid of it.

337
00:17:05,525 --> 00:17:06,442
Huh?

338
00:17:09,070 --> 00:17:11,531
-[grunts]
-[chains jangling]

339
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:20,957
Got it.

340
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:28,923
Later.

341
00:17:31,842 --> 00:17:33,302
[gasps]

342
00:17:37,557 --> 00:17:38,558
Hm?

343
00:17:39,684 --> 00:17:40,977
[Light] Why am I doing this?

344
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:42,645
I don't belong here.

345
00:17:43,312 --> 00:17:44,188
Ryuzaki.

346
00:17:44,689 --> 00:17:47,400
I realize that I was the one
pushing for confinement

347
00:17:47,483 --> 00:17:49,402
and that I asked you to put me in here.

348
00:17:49,527 --> 00:17:51,529
But I just realized something important.

349
00:17:51,737 --> 00:17:53,614
This whole thing is completely pointless.

350
00:17:53,823 --> 00:17:56,200
-Huh?
-[Light] Because I'm not Kira!

351
00:17:56,701 --> 00:17:58,452
You have to get me out of here!

352
00:17:59,245 --> 00:18:00,329
Hmm...

353
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:01,539
[L] I can't do that.

354
00:18:01,664 --> 00:18:04,250
I promised you that no matter
what you said, I wouldn't let you out

355
00:18:04,375 --> 00:18:06,669
until I was convinced
that you're not Kira.

356
00:18:07,670 --> 00:18:09,964
Please, L. I wasn’t thinking clearly.

357
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:12,633
Do you really think
that a serial killer like Kira

358
00:18:12,883 --> 00:18:15,303
could commit those crimes
without being aware of them?

359
00:18:15,970 --> 00:18:18,931
If I have no memory of his crimes,
I'm not him!

360
00:18:19,974 --> 00:18:21,892
I have never been able
to accept this idea

361
00:18:22,059 --> 00:18:24,812
that Kira has been acting
without self-awareness all this time.

362
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:27,064
But that doesn't change that fact

363
00:18:27,189 --> 00:18:29,358
that all the evidence
points to you being Kira.

364
00:18:30,067 --> 00:18:31,652
Since we imprisoned you,

365
00:18:31,819 --> 00:18:34,113
Kira hasn't committed a single murder.

366
00:18:35,072 --> 00:18:37,283
Listen, just hear me out.

367
00:18:37,408 --> 00:18:39,994
I swear to you, I am not lying.
You have to believe me.

368
00:18:40,453 --> 00:18:41,829
I'm not Kira!

369
00:18:42,288 --> 00:18:44,957
I must have been framed!
That's the only explanation for this.

370
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:47,710
[L] What's wrong with you, Light Yagami?

371
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:50,254
What you're saying is completely absurd.

372
00:18:50,421 --> 00:18:53,424
But, for some reason,
it feels believable to me.

373
00:18:53,841 --> 00:18:56,260
[Light] You have to let me out!
We're wasting time!

374
00:18:56,719 --> 00:18:58,471
[L] We can't let you out yet.

375
00:18:59,639 --> 00:19:00,765
[Light] Damn.

376
00:19:00,931 --> 00:19:02,308
Why is this happening?

377
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:04,185
What the hell is going on?

378
00:19:04,352 --> 00:19:05,895
This isn't like Light at all.

379
00:19:06,228 --> 00:19:07,730
He's contradicting himself.

380
00:19:08,064 --> 00:19:09,649
It doesn't make any sense to me.

381
00:19:10,191 --> 00:19:12,276
We can't release him
now that the murders have stopped.

382
00:19:12,735 --> 00:19:14,612
It doesn't matter what he says.

383
00:19:15,196 --> 00:19:17,198
I mean, even I know that much.

384
00:19:17,406 --> 00:19:19,158
Anyway, I don't care what anyone says,

385
00:19:19,241 --> 00:19:22,078
as far as I'm concerned,
we have all the proof we need.

386
00:19:22,244 --> 00:19:24,580
Light Yagami is Kira
and that's the end of it.

387
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:28,751
[Matsuda panting]

388
00:19:28,876 --> 00:19:30,169
FIFTEENTH DAY IN PRISON

389
00:19:30,252 --> 00:19:31,587
What's going on?

390
00:19:31,671 --> 00:19:34,799
I just heard two weeks’ worth of criminals
were just murdered all at once!

391
00:19:34,924 --> 00:19:36,008
It happened yesterday!

392
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:37,343
Yeah, Kira is back.

393
00:19:37,426 --> 00:19:38,386
KIRA STRIKES AGAIN

394
00:19:38,886 --> 00:19:40,513
So, did you guys already tell the Chief?

395
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,348
No, not yet.

396
00:19:43,766 --> 00:19:45,976
Guess what, Chief?
Kira has started killing again!

397
00:19:46,102 --> 00:19:47,019
What?

398
00:19:47,395 --> 00:19:49,438
It looks like Kira was only resting.

399
00:19:49,563 --> 00:19:51,774
But now he has started
punishing criminals again!

400
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:53,734
[Yagami] Is that true, Matsuda?

401
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:56,612
Then that means my son...

402
00:19:57,029 --> 00:19:59,573
I shouldn't be happy
that people have been killed but...

403
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:02,410
at least Light's name
will finally be cleared.

404
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:06,622
Wait, knowing Ryuzaki,
this won't be enough to clear him.

405
00:20:07,581 --> 00:20:08,708
[Matsuda and Aizawa] Hm?

406
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:11,711
Well, he's in the gray.

407
00:20:12,128 --> 00:20:13,713
Did you hear what he just said, Chief?

408
00:20:13,838 --> 00:20:16,549
[Yagami] Yeah, it's a hell of a lot better
than being completely guilty.

409
00:20:16,632 --> 00:20:17,633
Thank God.

410
00:20:17,717 --> 00:20:18,968
[Matsuda] I'm sure as grays go,

411
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:20,553
he's a shade closer to being cleared.

412
00:20:20,803 --> 00:20:22,763
-Let's tell Light!
-[L] Matsuda!

413
00:20:23,264 --> 00:20:25,224
I mean, please don't, Mr. Matsuda.

414
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:26,475
"Matsuda"?

415
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:28,978
We shouldn't tell him about this.

416
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:30,938
But... But why not?

417
00:20:32,022 --> 00:20:32,898
Hello, Light.

418
00:20:33,441 --> 00:20:34,775
[Light] What is it, Ryuzaki?

419
00:20:35,651 --> 00:20:37,486
You've been in here just over two weeks

420
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:39,697
and not a single new criminal
has been punished.

421
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:42,450
Now, why make this harder
than it has to be?

422
00:20:42,575 --> 00:20:43,784
Are you ready to confess?

423
00:20:43,951 --> 00:20:45,369
[Light] Don't be ridiculous.

424
00:20:45,745 --> 00:20:47,204
I'm telling you, you're wrong.

425
00:20:47,621 --> 00:20:49,206
I understand why you feel that way.

426
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:52,835
But even if the evidence does point to me,
I swear to you this is a set up!

427
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:54,503
I'm not Kira!

428
00:20:55,171 --> 00:20:58,007
Zoom in on me, if you want.
Go ahead, look at my eyes!

429
00:20:58,382 --> 00:20:59,425
You tell me,

430
00:20:59,550 --> 00:21:02,011
do these look like the eyes
of someone who's lying?

431
00:21:04,930 --> 00:21:08,559
[L] Amane, are you ready to tell me
who Kira is or not?

432
00:21:09,727 --> 00:21:11,604
What? That again?

433
00:21:11,854 --> 00:21:13,481
I wish I knew but I don't.

434
00:21:14,106 --> 00:21:15,399
Because, if I did,

435
00:21:15,483 --> 00:21:18,235
I'd thank him for punishing
the burglar who killed my parents.

436
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:19,987
To me, Kira is a hero.

437
00:21:20,863 --> 00:21:22,072
Hm...

438
00:21:25,117 --> 00:21:28,704
I don't understand what's going on here.

439
00:21:29,330 --> 00:21:36,337
TO BE CONTINUED

440
00:21:41,884 --> 00:21:46,931
[theme song playing]
